# 📊 My Portfolio Dashboard

A sleek, real-time, and stylish stock portfolio dashboard built with **Next.js 15** and **Tailwind CSS**, powered by a custom backend API. It fetches current stock prices (CMP), calculates gains/losses, and displays sector-wise and stock-wise breakdowns with charts, filters, dark mode, and Excel export.

---

## 🔧 Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** Next.js (App Router), Tailwind CSS, TypeScript
- **Backend:** Node.js + Express
- **Data Source:** Custom API (can be connected to real stock APIs)
- **Features:** Dark/Light mode, Export to Excel, Sector Filter, Gain/Loss Animations, Glossy UI

---

## 📁 Project Structure

My-Portfolio-Dashboard/
├── backend/ # Express.js server fetching CMP data
├── src/
│ ├── app/
│ │ ├── page.tsx # Main dashboard UI
│ │ ├── layout.tsx # Root layout
│ │ └── globals.css # Tailwind + custom styles (including background)
│ ├── data/
│ │ └── portfolio.ts # Portfolio stocks list
│ └── ...
├── public/ # Static assets
├── package.json
└── README.md



---

## 🚀 Live Features

- 🎨 modern UI with animated stock rows
- 🌗 Dark & Light mode toggle
- 🔍 Filter portfolio by sector
- 📤 Export portfolio to Excel (`.xlsx`)
- 📈 Real-time CMP update every 15 seconds
- 🧮 Gain/Loss with arrows (▲ ▼) and live number counters
- 🖼️ Background image support (editable in `globals.css`)

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### ✅ 1. Clone the Repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/vishnu0403/My-Portfolio-Dashboard.git
cd My-Portfolio-Dashboard

2. Install dependencies

frontend

cd frontend  # if using a separate folder, otherwise stay in root
npm install


Backend

cd backend
npm install


3. Start Backend Server

cd backend
npm run dev


4. Start Frontend (Next.js)
bash
Copy
Edit
cd frontend  # or stay in root if frontend is in root
npm run dev
